GERMISTON A memorial service for jazz legend, Thandi Klaasen was held at the Germiston City Hall on Wednesday.Klaasen died 10 days ago after a long battle with pancreatic cancer.She was 86 years old. Various government officials attended the memorial service.Klaasen will be buried on Friday at the Thomas Nkobi cemetery (formerly known as South Park) in Germiston.LISTEN: Thandi Klaasen - Sophiatown (YouTube.com/ndchance):Tweets about #KlaasenMemorial AND (FROM:@Nontobek0Sibisi since:2017-01-25 until:2017-01-26) eNCA